   "body" : "Please see the discussion of #15367 for detailed rationale. Essentially, the idea is to indicate, via creation of a file, that `bitcoind` is not only running but ready to actually use. This should provide a convenient way for scripts to reliably start `bitcoind`, wait for it to become ready, and then subsequently start any other services (e.g. `lnd`) that depend on it.\r\n\r\nThis PR also adds a `-ready` argument for specifying the name of the ready file (default: `$DATADIR/.ready`)\r\n",
